Claims CLAIMS What is claimed is: 1. A method comprising: identifying, by a processing device, a first dataset in a data store; identifying, by the processing device, a second dataset in the data store; tracking, by the processing device, updated data in rows of the first dataset using a first local marker; tracking, by the processing device, updated data in rows of the second dataset using a second local marker; performing, by the processing device, a join between the first dataset and the second dataset; creating, by the processing device, a materialized view using the join; identifying, by the processing device using the first local marker and the second local marker, updated data in one or more of: rows of the first dataset or rows of the second dataset; identifying, by the processing device, rows in the materialized view corresponding to the one or more rows of the first dataset and the second dataset having the identified updated data; and updating, by the processing device, the identified rows in the materialized view based on the identified updated data in the one or more rows of the first dataset and the second dataset. 2. The method of claim 1, wherein the first local marker comprises a first particular column in the first dataset to track one or more rows of the first dataset having one or more updated data, and wherein the second local marker comprises a second particular column in the second dataset to track one or more rows of the second dataset having another one or more updated data. 3. The method of claim 1, wherein the first local marker comprises a first data associated with a first data type, wherein a value of the first data is restricted to a first monotonically increasing value, and wherein the second local marker comprises a second data associated with a second data type, wherein a value of the second data is restricted to a second monotonically increasing value. 4. The method of claim 3, wherein the first data type and the second data type each comprises one or more of: a timestamp, a ROWVERSION, or serials. 5. The method of claim 1, wherein a transaction on the first dataset or the second dataset is configured to be limited to a bounded transaction. 6. The method of claim 5, wherein the bounded transaction comprises one or more of: a time-limited transaction, a size-limited transaction, or an action-limited transaction. 7. The method of claim 1, wherein the identifying the updated data comprises: comparing, by the processing device, each of the first local marker and the second local marker to a stored running tally marker. 8. A system comprising: a memory; and a processing device communicably coupled to the memory, the processing device to: identify a first dataset in a data store; identify a second dataset in the data store; track updated data in rows of the first dataset using a first local marker; track updated data in rows of the second dataset using a second local marker; perform a join between the first dataset and the second dataset; create a materialized view using the join; identify, using the first local marker and the second local marker, updates to data in one or more of: rows of the first dataset or rows of the second dataset; identify, rows in the materialized view corresponding to the one or more rows of the first dataset and the second dataset having the identified updated data; and update, the identified rows in the materialized view based on the identified updated data in the one or more rows of the first dataset and the second dataset. 9. The system of claim 8, wherein the first local marker comprises a first particular column in the first dataset to track one or more rows of the first dataset having one or more updated data, and wherein the second local marker comprises a second particular column in 

 the second dataset to track one or more rows of the second dataset having another one or more updated data. 10. The system of claim 8, wherein the first local marker comprises a first data associated with a first data type, wherein a value of the first data is restricted to a first monotonically increasing value, and wherein the second local marker comprises a second data associated with a second data type wherein a value of the second data is restricted to a second monotonically increasing value. 11. The system of claim 10, wherein the first data type and the second data type each comprises one or more of: a timestamp, a ROWVERSION, or serials. 12. The system of claim 8, wherein a transaction on the first dataset or the second dataset is configured to be limited to a bounded transaction. 13. The system of claim 12, wherein the bounded transaction comprises one or more of: a time-limited transaction, a size limited transaction, or an action limited transaction. 14. The system of claim 8, wherein to identify the updated the data, the processing device is to: compare each of the first local marker and the second local marker to one or more of a stored running tally marker. 15. A non-transitory machine-readable storage medium storing instructions that cause a processing device to: identify a first dataset in a data store; identify a second dataset in the data store; track updated data in rows of the first dataset using a first local marker; track updated data in rows of the second dataset using a second local marker; perform a join between the first dataset and the second dataset; create a materialized view using the join; identify, using the first local marker and the second local marker, updated data in one or more of: rows of the first dataset or rows of the second dataset; 

 identify, rows in the materialized view corresponding to the one or more rows of the first dataset and the second dataset having the identified updated data; and update, the identified rows in the materialized view based on the identified updated data in the one or more rows of the first dataset and the second dataset. 16. The non-transitory machine-readable storage medium of claim 15, wherein the first local marker comprises a first particular column in the first dataset to track one or more rows of the first dataset having one or more updated data, and wherein the second local marker comprises a second particular column in the second dataset to track one or more rows of the second dataset having another one or more updated data. 17. The non-transitory machine-readable storage medium of claim 15, wherein the first local marker comprises a first data associated with a first data type, wherein a value of the first data is restricted to a first monotonically increasing value, and wherein the second local marker comprises a second data associated with a second data type wherein a value of the second data is restricted to a second monotonically increasing value. 18. The non-transitory machine-readable storage medium of claim 17, wherein the first data type and the second data type each comprises one or more of: a timestamp, a ROWVERSION, or serials. 19. The non-transitory machine-readable storage medium of claim 15, wherein a transaction on the first dataset or the second dataset is configured to be limited to a bounded transaction. 20. The non-transitory machine-readable storage medium of claim 19, wherein the bounded transaction comprises one or more of: a time-limited transaction, a size-limited transaction, or an action-limited transaction.
